metadata.name: Griddy #112
metadata.description:
《Griddy》started from a survey of Mondrian’s and Raven Kwok’s work. During the process, several primitive elements are put together to form 《Griddy》.

The palette is chosen from RYB, RGB, CMYK. Three possible thicknesses are chosen for the grid line, and with a possibility of the same color with the background, forming a “negative space” effect. Three ratios for the partition of space, and with a possibility of “inverted ratio” when dividing space. For filling the grid, three prime numbers will be randomly selected for each color. And finally, a possibility that the whole grid moves.

Coding with the lovely Pts.js.

metadata.name: Flores del Mal #88
metadata.description:
"Flores del Mal" is a series of drawings about dead flowers and a solitary moon. The inspiration came from nature and the strange beauty of "Les fleurs du mal" by French author Charles Baudelaire.

Features
- 10 possible backgrounds
- 6 possible flower colors
- 3 possible moon colors
- 2 possible line colors
- 1 to 3 levels of flower and branch density

metadata.name: Ross Generator #44
metadata.description: As a child, I watched Bob Ross.  Instead of painting the pictures, I sketched them in pencil, then in ink.  I took inspiration from the beauty that emerged from a blank canvas.  In this generative work, I take to code to build an impression of Bob’s vision of nature in a “larger-than-life” wilderness scene.  Escape into the back-country.  Wander through lush valleys toward distant mountains.  Take in the scent of pine and dew-soak mosses.  Listen to the steady breeze whispering through the bows of furs, hemlocks and junipers.  Enjoy the peace, solitude and serenity of nature’s call with this masterful work.  Created using p5js.
